“We are very close to a return to the Pacific,” he promised late August.
But some analysts believe that the court would hardly take Bolivia’s side and that very little would change if it had.
The UN agency, which was held in the Netherlands, has no authority to give away Chilean rural areas and has suggested that it will not determine the outcome of any negotiations.
